{
  "texts": [
    "The first category is prohibited from being traded, for the next two categories the obligations imposed are proportionate to the category of risk, and for the last category there are currently no specific obligations proposed.",
    "Qualifying AI as high-risk under the Artificial Intelligence Act is dependent on the purpose of its usage.",
    "However, it is up to the user sometimes to decide on the use of the content, thus the user determines the category of the risk (Helberger & Diakopoulos, 2023, p. 2).",
    "(b) US regulatory approach on AI In October 2022 the White House Office of Science and Technology Policy developed a document called the Blueprint for an AI Bill of Rights, which contains a set of five guiding principles for the creation and use of AI systems.",
    "These principles have a status of soft law and are aimed at the protection of US citizens."
  ]
}